# CamMate – Handy Smart Camera Assistant Robot

**Step 1:** Servo bring-up on ESP32-WROOM-32 with two MG995 (front & 
rear).  
**Step 2:** Add wheels using L298N (files stubbed: `WheelControl.*`).

## Hardware
- ESP32-WROOM-32 Dev Board
- 2× MG995 servos (front & rear)
- External 5–6 V servo PSU (≥2 A recommended)
- (Later) L298N + 2 DC motors + separate motor PSU

## Wiring (Servos)
- MG995 V+ → external 5–6 V
- MG995 GND → external PSU GND
- **ESP32 GND → external PSU GND** (common ground)
- Front signal → GPIO 18
- Rear  signal → GPIO 19

> If ESP32 resets or servos twitch: PSU sag or missing common ground. Add 
1000–2200µF across servo PSU.

## Software
- Arduino IDE
- Board: `ESP32 Dev Module`
- Library: `ESP32Servo`

## Serial Commands
- `c`            – center both (90°)
- `sf`           – sweep FRONT 60..120
- `sr`           – sweep REAR  60..120
- `bf=ANG`       – set both to ANG (0..180)
- `ff=ANG`       – set front to ANG
- `fr=ANG`       – set rear  to ANG
- `mf=ANG`       – slow move front to ANG
- `mr=ANG`       – slow move rear  to ANG
- `help`         – show menu

